  "text": "Machine-based nuclei segmentation algorithms could yield nuclei with spiky boundaries due to imperfect processing modules and severe artifacts introduced in the image acquisition process. To address this problem reliably, we would like to regularize nuclei shapes in a manner that leverages both image data and model knowledge. For this purpose, the deformable model with Gradient Vector Flow (GVF) [CITATION_1] is used to regulate nuclear boundaries.",
